    {
      "question": "$PA$ and $PB$ are two tangents from a point $P$ to a circle with centre $O$ such that $\\angle APB = 80^\\circ$. Find $\\angle AOB$.",
      "answer": "$100^\\circ$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "In quadrilateral $OAPB$, the sum of opposite angles is $180^\\circ$ because the angles at $A$ and $B$ are $90^\\circ$ each.",
          "Calculate $\\angle AOB = 180^\\circ - \\angle APB$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\angle OAP = 90^\\circ, \\angle OBP = 90^\\circ \\\\ \\angle AOB + \\angle APB = 180^\\circ \\\\ \\angle AOB + 80^\\circ = 180^\\circ \\\\ \\angle AOB = 100^\\circ$"
      },
